## M19(4/6): calling an `unsafe` fn from a safe context is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35: an `unsafe sub`/`unsafe fun` declares
## that calling it requires the caller to be in an unsafe
## context. Without an enclosing `unsafe` block or an enclosing
## `unsafe` fn, the call is sema-rejected with a tailored
## diagnostic naming the callee and pointing at both fixes.

unsafe sub raw_op()
  print(1)

sub main()
  raw_op()         # error: call to unsafe function requires unsafe context
